Subject: [PATCH] Make Graphite Dawn Vulkan a fatal renderer contract

Nucleus products have one compositor renderer. Allow the GPU process to restart
on that renderer, but never downgrade to Ganesh, GL, or software compositing.
Initialization failure and exhaustion of Chromium's normal GPU crash budget
terminate the browser with a named renderer-contract failure.

diff --git a/content/browser/gpu/gpu_data_manager_impl_private.cc b/content/browser/gpu/gpu_data_manager_impl_private.cc
--- a/content/browser/gpu/gpu_data_manager_impl_private.cc
+++ b/content/browser/gpu/gpu_data_manager_impl_private.cc
